Losing a pet is never easy. When facing the sudden loss of a furry companion, pet owners might not know what to do if their pet dies at home.&nbsp;
While it may be unclear what best to do when experiencing such an ordeal, experts stress that it is important to take a second and grieve the loss.
“Acknowledge your feelings about that loss,” says Dr. Jennie Rubenstein, veterinarian and&nbsp; member of the New York State Veterinary Medical Society.

